+== EXAMPLES
+
+=== Interactively Rebasing the Last 4 Commits
+
+To interactively rebase the last 4 commits, use:
+
+-------------------------------------------------
+$ git rebase -i HEAD~4
+-------------------------------------------------
+
+This will open an editor with a list of the last 4 commits, allowing you to:
+- **pick** (keep commit as is)
+- **edit** (modify commit message or content)
+- **squash** (combine commits)
+- **reorder** (change commit sequence)
+
+Example: To squash the last two commits into one:
+
+1. Run:
+   $ git rebase -i HEAD~2
+
+2. Change the second commitâ€™s action from `pick` to `squash`:
+
+-------------------------------------------------
+pick abc123 Commit message 1
+squash def456 Commit message 2
+-------------------------------------------------
+
+3. Save and exit.
+4. Edit the new commit message if needed, then save.
